                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Conger</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1899-03-24">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 24, 1899</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Acting consul at Amoy, having asked whether to oppose Japanese concession, was
                    telegraphed March 9 to remonstrate against discrimination or interference with
                    legitimate American interests. This was intended to prevent possible transfer of
                    existing American rights to Japanese administration. He has not been instructed
                    to ask an American concession, but if China is disposed to grant separate
                    concessions at Amoy, we should expect no less consideration than other friendly
                    powers.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hay</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
